      "writtenOn": "2020-03-19T16:01:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "the return type of test.idSegs.pop() is string | undefined.\nSo if we check length,\nthe code would be\n```\nif (test.idSegs.length \u003d\u003d 0) {\n  this.tests.push(test.test);\n  return;\n}\nconst nextSeg \u003d test.idSegs.pop() as string;\n```\nWe need to cast string | undefined to string.\nI want to limit the usage of down casting as much as possible.\nI do agree that the gain is very marginal though.",
